01:32:25.880 --> 01:32:27.690
Let's talk about some of the
core features of App Engine.

01:32:27.690 --> 01:32:30.340
So in terms of serving web
requests, we have sort of a

01:32:30.340 --> 01:32:31.120
few core features.

01:32:31.120 --> 01:32:33.420
We have front ends for short
bursty requests, we have back

01:32:33.420 --> 01:32:36.590
end for long, long-limbed
requests, or maybe you want to

01:32:36.590 --> 01:32:38.410
run code in the background
a lot.

01:32:38.410 --> 01:32:40.920
Task Queues, to be able to queue
up work, and we Cron for

01:32:40.920 --> 01:32:41.760
scheduling.

01:32:41.760 --> 01:32:43.720
So there's some nice
features built in.

01:32:43.720 --> 01:32:46.320
From the storage layer, we
have a couple different

01:32:46.320 --> 01:32:46.820
technologies.

01:32:46.820 --> 01:32:51.410
We have our Data Store, which
is really our key values

01:32:51.410 --> 01:32:52.930
store, basically in the
cloud, very scalable.

01:32:52.930 --> 01:32:56.000
We have CloudSQL, which is a
MySQL in the cloud, as well as

01:32:56.000 --> 01:32:58.430
a high performance Memcache
layer to really aid

01:32:58.430 --> 01:33:00.070
performance.

01:33:00.070 --> 01:33:02.230
Services we have a number of
really powerful services.

01:33:02.230 --> 01:33:05.960
We have Users API, Mail API,
Image, URL Fetch, MapReduce, a

01:33:05.960 --> 01:33:07.750
really cool one called
TrafficSplitting, which

01:33:07.750 --> 01:33:10.300
actually lets you deploy
multiple versions of your

01:33:10.300 --> 01:33:13.610
applications and do AB testing
really simply.

01:33:13.610 --> 01:33:17.300
So the key thing here is that
all of these services, from

01:33:17.300 --> 01:33:21.340
the compute, storage, and users,
mail, et cetera, these

01:33:21.340 --> 01:33:22.770
are all managed for you.

01:33:22.770 --> 01:33:24.470
These are building blocks that
just run as a service.

01:33:24.470 --> 01:33:26.580
You don't have to configure and
