01:40:12.740 --> 01:40:15.510
stack that you have, some of
the software that you're

01:40:15.510 --> 01:40:16.450
using, you're used to.

01:40:16.450 --> 01:40:19.070
But there's going to be a point
where those tools may

01:40:19.070 --> 01:40:21.570
not work, and that's when you
get something like a billion,

01:40:21.570 --> 01:40:22.880
and now you've got a
big data problem.

01:40:22.880 --> 01:40:25.060
So what are some of the things
that you might have to do when

01:40:25.060 --> 01:40:27.220
you get to billions of records,

01:40:27.220 --> 01:40:27.950
gigabytes of gigabytes.

01:40:27.950 --> 01:40:30.450
Well, maybe you shard your
traditional MySQL database.

01:40:30.450 --> 01:40:33.590
Maybe you buy new software,
you're switching from one

01:40:33.590 --> 01:40:36.250
stack to another, you're going
from a relational model to a

01:40:36.250 --> 01:40:37.780
no SQL model.

01:40:37.780 --> 01:40:39.700
Or maybe you're preprocessing
data for analytics.

01:40:39.700 --> 01:40:43.270
So you're running your
traditional MySQL database

01:40:43.270 --> 01:40:46.090
overnight to get some
kind of results.

01:40:46.090 --> 01:40:47.570
And then maybe you need
more employee time or

01:40:47.570 --> 01:40:49.350
you need more employees.

01:40:49.350 --> 01:40:50.750
And that's when things
get a little crazy.

01:40:50.750 --> 01:40:52.410
Then your database starts
looking like the Borg

01:40:52.410 --> 01:40:54.450
spaceship and you've got
terabytes of data, and then

01:40:54.450 --> 01:40:56.160
you're in real trouble, because
then maybe you have to

01:40:56.160 --> 01:40:58.110
rethink your whole system.

01:40:58.110 --> 01:41:00.430
So let me tell you about
scale, right?

01:41:00.430 --> 01:41:03.090
So as you move from paradigm
to paradigm, what happens?

01:41:03.090 --> 01:41:07.190
Well, you can maybe predict the
cost of new storage, or

01:41:07.190 --> 01:41:09.660
instances, or virtual machines,
there may be a fixed

01:41:09.660 --> 01:41:10.660
cost there.

01:41:10.660 --> 01:41:12.850
But moving from gigabytes to
terabytes, moving from

01:41:12.850 --> 01:41:14.420
paradigm to paradigm,
