BigQuery?

01:42:08.530 --> 01:42:11.170
Google BigQuery is our
tool for analyzing

01:42:11.170 --> 01:42:12.330
massive data sets.

01:42:12.330 --> 01:42:15.040
It uses a SQL-style language
that you may already be used

01:42:15.040 --> 01:42:18.570
to, makes it easy to write
queries on this data.

01:42:18.570 --> 01:42:20.910
But the best part about it, as
a developer the thing I love

01:42:20.910 --> 01:42:23.160
is it's an API, it's
a service.

01:42:23.160 --> 01:42:26.130
You make calls to it via API,
you can use the programming

01:42:26.130 --> 01:42:28.890
language of your choice,
it's a RESTful API.

01:42:28.890 --> 01:42:30.350
So we use this technology
internally.

01:42:30.350 --> 01:42:31.770
We've written a few
papers about it.

01:42:31.770 --> 01:42:33.950
Internally, we call it Dremel,
and you can read the paper,

01:42:33.950 --> 01:42:35.260
the research paper we
published, if you're

01:42:35.260 --> 01:42:36.075
interested.

