02:00:03.930 --> 02:00:05.740
I guess quickly, let's
say you're on a

02:00:05.740 --> 02:00:07.660
multi-monitor system.

02:00:07.660 --> 02:00:10.980
And if you want to run a game,
you're going to want to run it

02:00:10.980 --> 02:00:13.190
full screen, like a first
person shooter.

02:00:13.190 --> 02:00:15.640
And when you bring your cursor
to the edge because you like

02:00:15.640 --> 02:00:19.210
looking left or looking right,
you don't want your cursor to

02:00:19.210 --> 02:00:21.260
go on to the next monitor,
you want it to be

02:00:21.260 --> 02:00:22.770
stuck there, right?

02:00:22.770 --> 02:00:25.970
So the Pointer Lock API allows
you to kind of define, this is

02:00:25.970 --> 02:00:27.790
the area in which
I'm operating.

02:00:27.790 --> 02:00:30.270
So first, you take
