02:00:30.270 --> 02:00:35.040
And then now, my cursor
is totally hidden.

02:00:35.040 --> 02:00:37.980
So the game can define its own
cursor if it wants, but you're

02:00:37.980 --> 02:00:41.180
probably just going to use
this for movement.

02:00:41.180 --> 02:00:45.210
And you can react, and you're
kind of stuck in full screen

02:00:45.210 --> 02:00:48.250
until you want to get out of it,
which is the behavior that

02:00:48.250 --> 02:00:50.770
you want when you're
building a game.

02:00:50.770 --> 02:00:54.370
So this was another
partnership.

02:00:54.370 --> 02:00:56.410
Some Google engineers got
together with some Mozilla

02:00:56.410 --> 02:00:59.420
engineers, banged this spec out
in like the course of two

02:00:59.420 --> 02:01:02.340
months, and it's implemented
across both now.

02:01:02.340 --> 02:01:06.610
Another one that a gaming
